claims:
2. The assembly monitoring method based on deep learning according to claim 1, wherein the step of creating a training set comprises:
establishing a 3D assembly body, comprising 3D models of parts and a positional relation between the parts;
annotating different parts in the 3D assembly body by different colors to establish an annotation model of the 3D assembly body;
defining an assembly sequence model, comprising defining parts contained in each assembly step; and
according to the assembly sequence model, loading annotation models of different parts, generating a 3D model and an annotation model for an assembly body corresponding to each assembly step, synthesizing a depth image set Di of the 3D assembly body at multiple monitoring angles by a depth buffer, and synthesizing a label image set Li by an imaging model of the depth camera, wherein i represents an assembly step, the depth image set a in the ith step corresponds to the label image set Li in the ith step, and in label images in the label image set Li, different parts of the 3D assembly body are rendered by different colors thus to establish a training set.
